# Implementation Log — goal-traceable-review

## What was implemented

- Added **Goal-traceability requirement** clause to both Layer 1 and Layer 2 prompt literals in `plugins/ai-driver/commands/run-spec.md`. Clauses are mirror-consistent semantically; the only differences are in surrounding context (subagent scope description vs Codex stdin-fence orientation).
- Added **Refinement-loop detection** section to Gating, placed between the scope-fence and the consensus steps. Includes term definitions for `normalized_location`, `previous round`, and `resolved`/`acknowledged` markers.
- Added CHANGELOG `[Unreleased]` `### Changed` entry with motivation (references the zh-CN template fix incident, 6 review rounds).

## Leveraged existing code

- Scope-fence demotion machinery in Gating — extended with new `[observation:refinement-loop]` tag; other demotion tags (`anchor-out-of-domain`, `no-anchor`) preserved byte-for-byte.
- Consensus dual-raise severity-notch rule — untouched, runs after refinement-loop demotion so it only applies to surviving actionable findings.
- `tests/review-synthesis/drift-demotion.sh` — existing anchor-demotion regression; AC-005 verifies it still passes after the Gating changes.

## Issues encountered

- Slash-command argument parsing: `/ai-driver:run-spec specs/foo.spec.md --accept-high` injects `--accept-high` into the spec path. The command template uses `$ARGUMENTS` as a single string. Worked around by manually parsing arguments. Unrelated to this spec's Goal; a separate PR can fix the template.
- Fish-shell interaction with `$(...)` and `|| echo 0` fallbacks produced false Layer 0 failures during self-check. Direct `grep` verified actual state. Unrelated to this spec; if future run-spec implementations shell out to check these rules, prefer bash over fish.

## Phase 0 artifact record (applying new rule retroactively)

For reference, the spec review transcript shows how the new rule would have applied to this PR's own review if it had been in place:
- Of 10 findings across L1+L2, 2 were Goal-critical (CT-001 contradiction, AMB-001 ambiguity) → fixed in spec v2
- 3 were not Goal-critical (AC-004 CHANGELOG wording, AC-003 drive-by match, L1 Info implementation detail) → would emit as `[observation:*]`
- 5 were legitimate concerns but structurally outside Level-A 5-AC scope → `--accept-high` acknowledgment

Under the new rule, round 1 would have surfaced 2 actionable findings + 3 observations + 5 acknowledgments. Six rounds would collapse to one.

